What's the output? let newList = [1, 2, 3].push(4); console.log(newList.push(5)); javascript A: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] B: [1, 2, 3, 5] C: [1, 2, 3, 4] D: Error Answer Answer: D The .push method returns the new length of the array, not the array itself! By setting newList equal to [1, 2, 3].push(4), we set newList equal to the new length of the array: 4. Then, we try to use the .push method on newList.
